{"body": "This is still an issue. Here is the simple test case. \r\n\r\nThe following will throw an error:\r\n\r\nDateTime.now.in_time_zone(\"Beijing\").to_json\r\n\r\nThe following will succeed:\r\n\r\nTime.now.in_time_zone(\"Beijing\").to_json\r\n\r\nI've updated the code to test for the method :usec instead of checking time's class. As for a unit test, it looks like one should go in activesupport/test/time_zone_test.rb, but I'm not exactly certain as to how to structure the test. Is it ok for my test to just throw an error if it fails?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/20242526", "created_at": "2013-06-30T05:29:52Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9562#issuecomment-20242526", "updated_at": "2013-06-30T05:29:52Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9562, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/huetsch", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f096acdbc66099ef0c623ce4c7f4b1f1?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdd35ead974250c14b9c9760460a52584.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/received_events", "gravatar_id": "f096acdbc66099ef0c623ce4c7f4b1f1", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "huetsch", "type": "User", "id": 121910, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huetsch/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e852bd3543c1510096cf"}, "id": 20242526, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9562"}
